Yes — here are the two Logger pipelines in the same style as your other projects.

I mirrored the same approval model using `ManualValidation@0` in agentless `server` jobs, sequenced with `dependsOn`, and used `and(succeeded(), ...)` on the deploy stage so approval success is preserved. ([Microsoft Learn][1])

I also kept `sit-temp` because that is what your old Logger pipeline was using. If this project now builds from `sit`, change the branch in the few places I noted below.

## 1) Build pipeline — Alterna Logger

Use this as your new build pipeline.

```yaml
name: LOGGER_SVC_SIT_$(Date:yyyyMMdd).$(Rev:r)

resources:
  repositories:
  - repository: templates
    type: git
    name: 'Azure Templates/Azure Templates'
    ref: refs/heads/main

trigger:
  branches:
    include:
    - sit-temp

pr: none

stages:
- stage: Build_Service
  displayName: 'Build & Publish Artifact'
  jobs:
  - template: pipelines/build-dotnet-core-webapi.yml@templates
    parameters:
      jobName: 'BuildLoggerService'
      jobDisplayName: 'Build Alterna Logger Service'
      buildPool: 'Build Pool'
      buildAgentName: 'UAT-ALTERNA-DK1'
      buildConfiguration: 'Release'
      restoreProjects: '**/*.csproj'
      runTests: false
      testProjects: ''
      publishProject: 'Logger/Logger.csproj'
      nugetConfigPath: 'nuget.config'
      zipName: 'Alterna-Logger-drop.zip'
      artifactName: 'logger-service-drop'
      publishOutputFolder: '$(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)\Alterna-Logger'
      deploymentMode: 'self-contained'
      targetRuntime: 'win-x64'
      produceSingleFile: true
      readyToRun: false
      trim: false
```

## 2) Release pipeline — Alterna Logger

Use this as your new release pipeline.

```yaml
name: LOGGER_REL_SIT_$(Date:yyyyMMdd).$(Rev:r)

parameters:
- name: deployService
  type: boolean
  default: false
  displayName: 'Deploy Logger Service'

- name: serviceBuildNumber
  type: string
  default: '__EMPTY__'
  displayName: 'Service Build Number'

resources:
  repositories:
  - repository: templates
    type: git
    name: 'Azure Templates/Azure Templates'
    ref: refs/heads/main

trigger: none
pr: none

variables:
- group: SIT_VARIABLE_GROUP

- name: servicePipelineName
  value: 'SIT - BUILD - SERVICE - Alterna Logger'

stages:

- stage: Resolve_Selected_Build
  displayName: 'Resolve selected build number'
  jobs:
  - job: ResolveBuildNumber
    displayName: 'Resolve pipeline name and build number'
    pool:
      name: 'Deployment Pool'
      demands:
      - Agent.Name -equals SIT-ALTERNA-BN1
    steps:
    - checkout: none

    - powershell: |
        $ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'

        $collectionUri = "$(System.CollectionUri)".TrimEnd('/')
        $projectName   = [System.Uri]::EscapeDataString("$(System.TeamProject)")
        $apiVersion    = '7.1'

        $headers = @{
          Authorization = "Bearer $env:SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN"
        }

        $deployService = "${{ parameters.deployService }}".ToLower() -eq 'true'

        if (-not $deployService) {
          throw 'At least one deployment target must be selected: Logger Service.'
        }

        function Normalize-BuildNumber {
          param([string]$BuildNumber)

          if ($BuildNumber -eq '__EMPTY__') {
            return ''
          }

          return $BuildNumber
        }

        function Resolve-DefinitionIdByName {
          param(
            [string]$Label,
            [string]$PipelineName
          )

          if ([string]::IsNullOrWhiteSpace($PipelineName)) {
            throw "$Label pipeline name is empty."
          }

          $encodedName = [System.Uri]::EscapeDataString($PipelineName)
          $uri = "{0}/{1}/_apis/build/definitions?name={2}&includeAllProperties=false&includeLatestBuilds=false&api-version={3}" -f `
            $collectionUri,
            $projectName,
            $encodedName,
            $apiVersion

          Write-Host "Resolving $Label pipeline name [$PipelineName]"
          $response = Invoke-RestMethod -Method Get -Uri $uri -Headers $headers

          if (-not $response.value -or $response.count -lt 1) {
            throw "No pipeline definition found for $Label with name [$PipelineName]."
          }

          $exactMatches = @($response.value | Where-Object { $_.name -eq $PipelineName })

          if ($exactMatches.Count -eq 0) {
            throw "No exact pipeline definition match found for $Label with name [$PipelineName]."
          }

          if ($exactMatches.Count -gt 1) {
            throw "More than one exact pipeline definition match was found for [$PipelineName]. Make the pipeline name unique."
          }

          $definition = $exactMatches[0]

          Write-Host "$Label definition resolved:"
          Write-Host "  Definition ID   = $($definition.id)"
          Write-Host "  Definition Name = $($definition.name)"

          return $definition.id
        }

        function Resolve-Build {
          param(
            [string]$Label,
            [string]$PipelineName,
            [string]$BuildNumber
          )

          $BuildNumber = Normalize-BuildNumber -BuildNumber $BuildNumber

          if ([string]::IsNullOrWhiteSpace($BuildNumber)) {
            throw "$Label build number is required because deployment of $Label was selected."
          }

          $definitionId = Resolve-DefinitionIdByName -Label $Label -PipelineName $PipelineName
          $encodedBuildNumber = [System.Uri]::EscapeDataString($BuildNumber)

          $uri = "{0}/{1}/_apis/build/builds?definitions={2}&buildNumber={3}&statusFilter=completed&resultFilter=succeeded&`$top=1&queryOrder=finishTimeDescending&api-version={4}" -f `
            $collectionUri,
            $projectName,
            $definitionId,
            $encodedBuildNumber,
            $apiVersion

          Write-Host "Resolving $Label build number [$BuildNumber] using pipeline definition [$definitionId]"
          $response = Invoke-RestMethod -Method Get -Uri $uri -Headers $headers

          if (-not $response.value -or $response.count -lt 1) {
            throw "No succeeded build found for $Label with build number [$BuildNumber] in pipeline [$PipelineName]."
          }

          $build = $response.value[0]

          if ($build.sourceBranch -ne 'refs/heads/sit-temp') {
            throw "$Label build [$BuildNumber] was resolved, but it belongs to branch [$($build.sourceBranch)] instead of [refs/heads/sit-temp]."
          }

          Write-Host "$Label build resolved:"
          Write-Host "  Build ID         = $($build.id)"
          Write-Host "  Build Number     = $($build.buildNumber)"
          Write-Host "  Definition ID    = $definitionId"
          Write-Host "  Definition Name  = $PipelineName"
          Write-Host "  Branch           = $($build.sourceBranch)"

          Write-Host "##vso[task.setvariable variable=${Label}PipelineDefinitionId;isOutput=true]$definitionId"
          Write-Host "##vso[task.setvariable variable=${Label}BuildId;isOutput=true]$($build.id)"
          Write-Host "##vso[task.setvariable variable=${Label}ResolvedBuildNumber;isOutput=true]$($build.buildNumber)"
        }

        Resolve-Build -Label 'Service' -PipelineName '$(servicePipelineName)' -BuildNumber '${{ parameters.serviceBuildNumber }}'
      name: Resolve
      displayName: 'Resolve pipeline name and build number'
      env:
        SYSTEM_ACCESSTOKEN: $(System.AccessToken)

- stage: Approval_SIT_Release
  displayName: 'Approval for SIT release'
  dependsOn:
  - Resolve_Selected_Build
  condition: succeeded('Resolve_Selected_Build')
  jobs:
  - job: WaitForBusinessApproval
    displayName: 'Wait for Business Approval'
    pool: server
    timeoutInMinutes: 1500
    steps:
    - task: ManualValidation@0
      timeoutInMinutes: 1440
      inputs:
        notifyUsers: 'SGBL\pabouserhal'
        instructions: 'Approve SIT Alterna Logger deployment.'
        onTimeout: 'reject'

  - job: WaitForManagementApproval
    displayName: 'Wait for Management Approval'
    dependsOn: WaitForBusinessApproval
    pool: server
    timeoutInMinutes: 1500
    steps:
    - task: ManualValidation@0
      timeoutInMinutes: 1440
      inputs:
        notifyUsers: 'SGBL\kabbas'
        instructions: 'Approve SIT Alterna Logger deployment.'
        onTimeout: 'reject'

- stage: Deploy_Service_SIT
  displayName: 'Deploy Logger Service to SIT'
  dependsOn:
  - Resolve_Selected_Build
  - Approval_SIT_Release
  condition: and(succeeded(), eq('${{ parameters.deployService }}', 'true'))
  variables:
    ServicePipelineDefinitionId: $[ stageDependencies.Resolve_Selected_Build.ResolveBuildNumber.outputs['Resolve.ServicePipelineDefinitionId'] ]
    ServiceBuildId: $[ stageDependencies.Resolve_Selected_Build.ResolveBuildNumber.outputs['Resolve.ServiceBuildId'] ]
  jobs:
  - template: pipelines/deploy-windows-service.yml@templates
    parameters:
      jobDependsOn: []
      jobCondition: succeeded()
      deploymentName: 'DeployLoggerService'
      deploymentDisplayName: 'Deploy Alterna Logger Windows Service - SIT'
      environmentName: 'SIT'
      deployPool: 'Deployment Pool'
      deployAgentName: 'SIT-ALTERNA-BN1'
      variableGroup: 'SIT_VARIABLE_GROUP'
      componentName: 'LOGGER'
      artifactName: 'logger-service-drop'
      artifactBuildType: 'specific'
      artifactProject: '$(System.TeamProject)'
      artifactDefinitionId: '$(ServicePipelineDefinitionId)'
      artifactBuildId: '$(ServiceBuildId)'
      artifactBranch: 'refs/heads/sit-temp'
      zipName: 'Alterna-Logger-drop.zip'
      serviceName: 'LoggerServiceAzureDevOps'
      serviceTargetPath: 'C:\Alterna-Backend-Services\AlternaLoggerAzureDevOps'
      cleanTargetBeforeCopy: true
      cleanExcludeCsv: 'logs,Keys'
      enableJsonTransform: true
      jsonFiles: '**/appsettings.json'
      enableXmlConfigTransform: false
      xmlConfigFiles: []
      xmlVariableValues: {}
      enableCustomXmlEdits: false
      customXmlEdits: []
      customXmlVariableValues: {}
      enableHealthCheck: false
      enableRollbackOnHealthCheckFailure: true
      enableLocalBackup: true
      backupRoot: 'C:\DeployBackups'
      backupPath: 'C:\DeployBackups\SIT\LOGGER\$(Build.BuildId)'

- stage: Tag_SERVICE_LKG_SIT
  displayName: 'Tag successful service build as LKG'
  dependsOn:
  - Resolve_Selected_Build
  - Deploy_Service_SIT
  condition: and(succeeded('Deploy_Service_SIT'), eq('${{ parameters.deployService }}', 'true'))
  variables:
    ServiceBuildId: $[ stageDependencies.Resolve_Selected_Build.ResolveBuildNumber.outputs['Resolve.ServiceBuildId'] ]
    ServicePipelineDefinitionId: $[ stageDependencies.Resolve_Selected_Build.ResolveBuildNumber.outputs['Resolve.ServicePipelineDefinitionId'] ]
  jobs:
  - job: TagServiceBuild
    displayName: 'Tag service build'
    pool:
      name: 'Deployment Pool'
      demands:
      - Agent.Name -equals SIT-ALTERNA-BN1
    steps:
    - checkout: none

    - template: pipelines/tag-builds.yml@templates
      parameters:
        tagTargets:
        - name: 'Alterna Logger Service'
          buildId: '$(ServiceBuildId)'
          definitionId: '$(ServicePipelineDefinitionId)'
          deployedTag: 'DEPLOYED-SIT-LOGGER-SVC'
          lkgTag: 'LKG-SIT-LOGGER-SVC'
          makeLkgUnique: true
```

Two important notes.

I used the **current** `deploy-windows-service.yml` shape you standardized later in the chat. That means I did **not** include the old parameters like:

* `serviceDisplayName`
* `serviceDescription`
* `serviceExeName`
* `serviceStartType`
* `createServiceIfMissing`
* `updateBinPathIfExists`

So this release pipeline assumes the Windows service already exists and only needs stop/copy/start deployment.

Also, I set `enableHealthCheck: false` because your old Logger service pipeline did not show an HTTP health endpoint. If Logger exposes one, we can turn it on and wire rollback to it too.

If your Logger repo now uses `sit` instead of `sit-temp`, change these 3 places:

* build pipeline trigger branch
* release pipeline branch validation in `Resolve-Build`
* release pipeline `artifactBranch` value

